      {
        "id": 2330175,
        "name": "JW Boyden",
        "username": "JW_Boyden",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/d2c977/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2018-01-05T17:49:15.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Opened one of these yesterday to see which side of the coin I came down on. The fruit here is massive for a Burgundy. My friend initially thought I served him a west coast pinot when tasted blind. If you look hard enough behind the fruit you do get Gevrey spice, some mineral, and the texture is reasonably silky like most Fourrier wines. With air the fruit seemed to move to a more stewed/cooked character. I am going to let my remaining bottles sit for some time and see if these can shed some baby fat and come into a bit better balance for my palate.</p>",
